agni invedic =\r\nrituals (srauta\nkarmas) where agni is involved. vedic rituals (srautakarmas=\r\n) can be\neither aupaasana&#39;s which include daily homa/pitru yaGYa&#39;setc..., a=\r\ngni\nfor samskaaras, agni for major yaGYas namely the 14 yaGYas -\nthesapta-h=\r\navir-yaGYa&#39;s (7) and the sapta-soma-yaGYa&#39;s (7).\n\n    srauta agni is the pr=\r\notector of house of thesadhaka, and hence it is\nalso termed as gRRiha-pati[=\r\ngriha=3Dhouse, pati=3Dmaster]agni (or)\ngaarhapatyagni. gaarhapatyagni is ma=\r\nintained in center of sadhakashome,\nand whenever agni is needed for aupaasa=\r\nna for daily\nhomam/saMskaaraasetc... some portion of gaarhapatyagni is tran=\r\nsferred to\nthe square shaped kuNdaon eastern side - this portion of agni\ntr=\r\nansferred to eastern side kuNda isnamed &quot;aahavaniiya agni&quot; [aa-havana\n=3D o=\r\nffering an oblation - sincethis agni is used for havyaM - oblations\nthat ar=\r\ne carried to devatas byhavyavaahana], this homa kuNda is used for\ndaivika k=\r\naaryaas.\n\n    For pitru kaaryaas a portion of agni fromgaarhapatyagni is\ntr=\r\nansferred to a semi-circular kuNDa on the right side of it,i.e. to a\nkuNDa =\r\nto the south of gaarhapaati kuNDa, this portion of agni istermed\ndakshinaag=\r\nni (agni transferred to right[dakshina]/south[dakshina] -\nthisagni is used =\r\nfor kavyaM - oblations that are carried to pitru\ndevataas bykavyavaahana), =\r\nit is placed to south since that is the\ndirection governed byyama and south=\r\n is the region of pitru devataas.\n\n   A schematic of above is provided here=\r\n -\n\n      smaarta agni - never divided [eka agni] also known as vivaha agni=\r\n\n(because it was given at marriagetime)\n\n                                  =\r\n      |\n\n                                        |\n\n              srauta ag=\r\nni - divided into three - hence also named treta\nagni\n\n                    =\r\n                    |\n\n             ---------------------------------------=\r\n---------------\n\n            |                           |                 =\r\n         |\n\n     aahavaniiya-agni                 gaarhapatiya-agni        =\r\n   \ndakshina-agni\n\n      (east)                                            =\r\n          \n(south)\n\n\n\n   Coming back to the rik -\n\n    Sitting[nidhishu] so=\r\nuth[dakShiNa]/to theright(of\ngaarhapatyagni)[dakShina] and with bent knees =\r\n- the left knee. inpitru\nsamskaaraas the auspicious direction is reversed, =\r\ni.e.\nyaGYopaveetam(sacred thread) will be in the opposite direction [the kn=\r\not\nwill be on leftside below shoulder], the left knee is placed on ground.\n=\r\n\n     With the bent knee, facing the south we areperforming this pitru\nkaar=\r\nya, the pitru devataas (vishve - all pitru devataas)who are invoked\nin earl=\r\nier riks are now asked to accept the offerings and\nyaGYaauspiciously - and =\r\nalso to bless for progeny, sinless peace etc...\n\n     While the yaGYa is pe=\r\nrformed we also prayto pitru devataas to not\nhurt us for any sins that we m=\r\nay have committed infrail i.e. by humanly\nmistakes, mistakes being weak in =\r\nbody and health\n(hencearapaH[health/free from diseases and sin] dadhaata[ma=\r\ny grant] was\nasked for in10.015.04), and mistakes commited because of moral=\r\n weakness.\nmoral weakness canbe because of not adhering to the rituals - re=\r\nasons\nbeing - procrastination,shadripus [kaama (desire), krodha(anger),\nlob=\r\nha(greed), moha(delusion),mada(morale-less passion),\nmaatsarya(jealous)] an=\r\nd aShTa paashas [ghRRiNa(hate), lajjaa (shame),\nbhaya (fear, shankaa(doubt)=\r\n, jugupsa(censure/reproach),kula(caste),\njaati(creed) and sheela (modesty)]=\r\n.\n\n\n\n  references: The Internet, Vedic reader by A.A. MacDonell, Monier\nWil=\r\nliams andMac Donell dictionaries via Mudgala Kosha, Roots and\nVerb-Forms by=\r\n W.D.Whitney, Vedic Grammar by AA MacDonell, all these\nreferences are freel=\r\nyavailable on the internet.\n\n\n\n